plaintext:
I notice that the grayliner theme I'm using loads this highlight.js library
which seems to be able to detect what language I'm typing in automatically and
highlight syntax according to that specific language. Let's see how it looks.

Just wrap the code in <pre> <code> </code> </pre>

C++


#include 

int main()
{
    std::cout << "Hello, world!\n";
}



Java


public class HelloWorld {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        // Prints "Hello, World" to the terminal window.
        System.out.println("Hello, World");
    }

}


JavaScript


alert('Hello, World!')


Python


print("Hello, world")



--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The result looks pretty good, except <iostream> is swallowed in my C++ snippet,
probably by ghost not highlight.js. I can change the tags into &lt; and &gt; 
manually, not sure if there's better way.

